727602f-a.text:
Northern Boulevard, south side, between 77th and 79th treets, showing in the center of the view the home of F.D. Richardson in 1873. J. Fowler was the owner in 1891. In 1920 it was the Jackson Heights Community Club House. It is not
standing in 1938.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

727601f-a.text:
Northern Boulevard, north side, east and west of 77th Street (extends northward between the two buildings). In the foreground at the side of J. Pack's roadhouse of 1891 extended Trains Meadow Road, which was discontinued in 1908 as a street. View number two looking eastward shows the old Jackson Avenue before it was widened and
renamed.
March 1924
Views 1 and 2
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
